						               													<description>Easy to play and dynamic at the same time!&amp;#10;Each player is to collect the best set of cards.&amp;#10;The players have their cards open. It's your decision to go forward or prevent any opponent's move.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every turn the host opens the cards and places them in a row.&amp;#10;7 cards for 3 players and 4 cards for 4 players.&amp;#10;Then he puts card-dividers to break the row into 3 segments as he likes.&amp;#10;Each player chooses which segment he would like to get - white, blue or black - and places a card of such color facedown&amp;#10;The host opens this cards and the players distribute the cards in a segment.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If:&amp;#10;A) any segment is not in demand, it&amp;rsquo;s put off&amp;#10;B) a segment is chosen by 1 player; he takes it for himself&amp;#10;C) a segment is chosen by 2 players, they are dividing this segment and voting again!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players stack the received cards at their face value, the role of the host is passed clockwise, and the new round begins.&amp;#10;        &amp;#10;The game ends when the deck runs out of cards. If a player has more cards with the same number on than others, he will receive a number of VP equal to this number. Whoever gains the most VP wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Number of the cards in the game is equal to it's Value. &amp;#10;10 cards of &amp;quot;10&amp;quot;, 9 cards of &amp;quot;9&amp;quot; and so on.&amp;#10;Also there are 15 Jokers, that players can use as any other value in their stock.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
